						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pallava, Nantivarmaṉ III, Year 6 = 852 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>In verse form. Built in and portions missing. The king is called Danti Nantivarman, meaning Nantivarman, son of Danti. He is also called Pallavamahārādhirāja. Refers to a Veḷḷāḷa and <hi rend="italic">Peruṅgāviti.</hi> Seems to be some gift to Nandimaṅgai (Nandimaṅgalam) by a Māṟpiḍugu-Iḷaṅgōvēḷār's son-in-law Viḻuppēraraiyaṉ Chāttaṉ, lord of Chelli.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> vol. XII No. 48 and AR. No. 88 of 1910.]</p>						

						</summary>
